SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12387
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract For a class of standard and widely used preferences, a one-shot money injection in a standard matching model can induce a significant and persistent output response by dispersing the distribution of wealth. Decentralized trade matters for both persistence and significance. Following the injection, the price response may be sluggish, the markup may move up with output, and both the interest rate and the inflation rate may drop below their trend levels.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - LEARNING IN A HEDONIC FRAMEWORK: VALUING BROWNFIELD REMEDIATION
AU  - Ma, Lala
Y1  - 2019/08/01
PY  - 2019
DA  - 2019/08/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12389
T2  - International Economic Review
